text: 85 to Africa is the second studio album by Nigerian-American recording artist Jidenna. It was released on August 23, 2019 through Wondaland Records and Epic Records. The album follows the release of his debut album The Chief, and the EP, Boomerang. The album features guest appearances from GoldLink, St. Beauty, Mr Eazi, Mereba and Seun Kuti. 85 to Africa charted at number 112 on the Billboard 200 chart, making it his lowest selling album to date. ==Track listing== Notes * – signifies a co-producer ==Release history== {| class="wikitable plainrowheaders" |- ! scope="col"| Region ! scope="col"| Date ! scope="col"| Format ! scope="col"| Label ! scope="col"| |- ! scope="row" rowspan="2"| Various | August 23, 2019 | | rowspan="2"|Epic | |- | March 6, 2020 | Vinyl | |} ==Charts== {| class="wikitable plainrowheaders" style="text- align:center" |+Chart performance for 85 to Africa |- ! scope="col"| Chart (2019) ! scope="col"| Peak position |- |- !US Top Album Sales (Billboard) |47 |} ==References== Category:2019 albums Category:Jidenna albums Category:Epic Records
